  "text": "Bug data. One possible application of Covrig is finding useful data about software bugs and correlating them with the static and dynamic metrics collected. For our study, we mined bug data from both software repositories and, where available, bug tracking systems. We automatically obtained a list of candidate bug-fixing revisions by iterating through the list of commits and checking the commit message for words such as fix, bug or issue, followed by a number representing the bug identifier. For example, a typical Memcached bug fix commit message looks like \"Issue 224 -check retval of main event loop\". The regular expression that we used to identify these commits is similar to the ones used in prior work [CITATION_1] : (?:bug|issue|fix|resolve|close)\\s*\\#?\\s?(\\d+)",
